House Resolution 439
By: Representatives Jones of the 143rd, Herring of the 145th, Griffin of the 149th, Paris of the
142nd, and Washburn of the 144th
A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating the Northeast High School Raiders football team for participating in the 2024
2 GHSA Class A Division 1 State Championship; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Raiders football team of Northeast High School in Macon, Georgia, has
4 demonstrated extraordinary skill, determination, and sportsmanship throughout the 2024
5 season; and
6 WHEREAS, under the exceptional leadership of Head Coach Jeremy Wiggins, the Northeast
7 Raiders achieved a remarkable 12-3 record, showcasing their talent and dedication on the
8 field; and
9 WHEREAS, the Raiders made history by advancing to the GHSA Class A Division 1 State
10 Championship game for the first time in school history, bringing pride and excitement to the
11 East Macon community; and
12 WHEREAS, the team's success was built on the outstanding performances of key players
13 such as senior running back Nick Woodford, who amassed 2,494 yards and 41 total
14 touchdowns, nearly breaking the county single-season rushing record; junior quarterback
15 Reginald "Bam" Glover, who achieved both 1,000 rushing and 1,000 passing yards in the
