16 season; senior linebacker Santana Balkcom, who averaged nearly 10 tackles and 2.5 sacks
17 per game; junior linebacker Tailen Sampson, who consistently contributed eight tackles per
18 game; and Kortnei Williams, who demonstrated exceptional defensive skills with an
19 impressive 10 interceptions; and
20 WHEREAS, the Northeast Raiders' journey to the state championship game united the
21 community, inspiring students from elementary to high school and reigniting Raider pride
22 throughout East Macon; and
23 WHEREAS, the team's historic season included hosting the first Macon home semifinal
24 game since 1975, defeating Fitzgerald 46-14 in a commanding performance; and
25 WHEREAS, the Northeast Raiders' achievements extend beyond the field as they have
26 become role models for perseverance, teamwork, and academic excellence, embodying the
27 true spirit of student-athletes.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body congratulate the Northeast High School Raiders football team upon
30 its outstanding 2024 season, its historic run to the state championship game, and its positive
31 impact on the community as well as celebrate its achievements and the bright future it
32 represents for Macon-Bibb County.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the
35 Northeast High School Raiders football team.
